      "comment_id" : 19009164,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "<code>anyVararg()</code> has Object as its return type. To make it compatible with any var arg types (e.g. String ..., Integer ..., etc.), do an explicit casting. For example, if you have <code>doSomething(Integer number, String ... args)</code> you can do the mock/stub code with something like <code>when(mock).doSomething(eq(1), (String) anyVarargs())</code>. That should take care of the compilation error."
