    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1690292362,
    "last_edit_date" : 1690292362,
    "creation_date" : 1689859653,
    "answer_id" : 76730393,
    "question_id" : 2631596,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I've looked up for various ways but most of the ways are not working as described. What worked for me is.</p>\n<p><strong>Method Signature:</strong></p>\n<p><code>ReturnType someMethod(String... strings)</code></p>\n<p><strong>Mockito to handle above method:</strong></p>\n<p><code>when(someMethod((String[])Mockito.any())).thenReturn(dummyReturnTypeObject);</code></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/ZVEfo.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">mocking a method with varargs</a></p>\n<p>if your mock is successful then the value that appears for the mocked step <em>wouldn't be null</em></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/UwLpz.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">result of mocking a method with varargs</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7361132,
      "reputation" : 836,
      "user_id" : 6579203,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/l60et.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "xtermi2",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6579203/xtermi2"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 24,
    "last_activity_date" : 1702082908,
    "last_edit_date" : 1702082908,
    "creation_date" : 1694009903,
    "answer_id" : 77052796,
    "question_id" : 2631596,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>With Mockito 5 <code>any()</code> does not match varargs in our project. In Mockito 4 this has worked.\nIn Mockito 5 now only <code>any(&lt;VAR-ARG-TYPE&gt;[].class)</code> does match varargs!</p>\n<p>Translated to your example this works in Mockito 5:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>when(a.b(anyInt(), anyInt(), any(C[].class))).thenReturn(b);\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
