  "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/questions/2631596/how-to-properly-match-varargs-in-mockito",
  "title" : "How to properly match varargs in Mockito",
  "body" : "<p>I've been trying to get to mock a method with vararg parameters using Mockito:</p>\n\n<pre><code>interface A {\n  B b(int x, int y, C... c);\n}\n\nA a = mock(A.class);\nB b = mock(B.class);\n\nwhen(a.b(anyInt(), anyInt(), any(C[].class))).thenReturn(b);\nassertEquals(b, a.b(1, 2));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This doesn't work, however if I do this instead:</p>\n\n<pre><code>when(a.b(anyInt(), anyInt())).thenReturn(b);\nassertEquals(b, a.b(1, 2));\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This works, despite that I have completely omitted the varargs argument when stubbing the method.</p>\n\n<p>Any clues?</p>\n"
}